episodes.title: How a Political Movement Slips Into Cult Territory and Dies
episodes.description:
A movement becomes a cult long before it collapses.

A political movement doesn’t fall apart all at once — it erodes when it slips into cult territory. Authority stops landing, the emotional high fades, and people quietly reclaim their judgment. This video breaks down how that unraveling happens and why so many former loyalists are stepping back now.
